1. Docker Compose (/opt/ollama/docker-compose.yml)
YAML
services:
  ollama:
    image: ollama/ollama:latest
    container_name: ollama
    restart: always
    ports:
      - "11434:11434"
    volumes:
      - ./ollama_data:/root/.ollama

  ollama-webui:
    image: ghcr.io/open-webui/open-webui:main
    container_name: ollama-webui
    restart: always
    ports:
      - "3000:8080"
    environment:
      - OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://ollama:11434
    volumes:
      - ./webui_data:/app/backend/data
2. Custom Integration Script (custom-ollama.py)
Location: /opt/soc/nusantara/wazuh/custom-integrations/custom-ollama.py

Python
#!/usr/bin/env python3
import sys
import json
import requests

alert_file = sys.argv[1]
ollama_url = "http://192.168.10.2:11434/api/generate"

with open(alert_file) as f:
    alert_json = json.load(f)

description = alert_json.get('rule', {}).get('description', 'No description')
level = alert_json.get('rule', {}).get('level', 0)
agent = alert_json.get('agent', {}).get('name', 'Unknown')
full_log = alert_json.get('full_log', '')

prompt = (
    f"Analyze this security alert. "
    f"Rule: {description}. Level: {level}. Agent: {agent}. "
    f"Log: {full_log}. "
    f"Provide a brief threat assessment."
)

payload = {
    "model": "llama3",
    "prompt": prompt,
    "stream": False
}

try:
    response = requests.post(ollama_url, json=payload, timeout=30)
    if response.status_code == 200:
        print(response.json().get('response'))
except Exception as e:
    print(f"Error: {str(e)}")
3. Permissions
Bash
chmod +x /opt/soc/nusantara/wazuh/custom-integrations/custom-ollama.py
chown root:root /opt/soc/nusantara/wazuh/custom-integrations/custom-ollama.py
4. Wazuh Configuration (ossec.conf)
Add this block to your manager configuration:

XML
<integration>
  <name>custom-ollama</name>
  <level>10</level>
  <alert_format>json</alert_format>
</integration>
5. Initialization Commands
Run these commands to start the stack and download the model:

Bash
cd /opt/ollama
docker-compose up -d
docker exec -it ollama ollama run llama3
Finally, restart your Wazuh manager container:

Bash
docker-compose -f /opt/soc/nusantara/wazuh/docker-compose.yml restart wazuh.manager
